subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis:
Scutum subrectangular (
Fig. 24B
). Ocularium in the middle of prosoma, very low, unarmed (
Figs 24C
, 
25C
). Femur IV in males slightly thicker than in females (
Fig. 25A
). Stigmatic area longer in males (
Fig. 25B
). Male genitalia: pars distalis not swollen in the middle portion, apical margin with a median notch. With more than ten pairs of lateral setae, small, more than seven pairs of ventral microsetae along lateral margins of pars distalis. Two pairs of parastylar setae. Follis barely longer than wide. Spiniform projections small, not clearly visible (
Fig. 26
).

